rComments: Prof. Eckenwalder's "Plants As We See Them" course is the BEST option for an easy breadth requirement. NO EXAM. Two powerpoint presentations, two essays, and minimal participation. One presentationessay is based on the "text" (I use this term loosely). Another is based on a "flavour plant". He lets class out early. Always. Easiest. grade. ever.

Took a seminar called 'Plants as we see them'; very easy course, and a good way to get your breadth requirement for science. The prof. is very nice and I found him to be an easy marker. The only catch, is that the course can get dry at times but it's still worth it.
Boring at times; need to write down EVERYTHING this man says.  a lot more charming/funny in a smaller class/lab setting. one of my fave profs this year
really liked the guy, very nice, tests were ok, very very nerdy, he must have been picked last in every gym class

Not as boring as some people claim. Tests are super hard and confusing. Plus, his test questions don't really have anything to do with what he talks about in lecture. Definitely one to record and listen to a second time.

Knows his material very well. Lectures are a little disorganized at times. Can be a wee bit boring on occasion. Overall, though, a pretty good prof. A tip: record his lectures and listen to them a second time to get more info out of them.
He is the most boring professor ever. He even looks like Darwin and I mean, he probably knows everything there is to know about Evolution and Darwin. But I bet he hates to teach it.
other students complained because of his voice, but i found his lectures very interesting with clear examples. useful required reading selections. a charming man!
really organized and enthusiastic. the test was on the hard side, but overall a really good prof.
A very good Professor.
Knowledgeable but sleep-inducing. Material fairly easy, test was fair. Torture to listen to. Would benefit from stimulant drugs. Seemed harmless enough.
Eckenwalder knows his stuff.  He just seems to hate teaching and therefore puts no effort into it whatsoever.
worst bio prof ever.
a good prof that knew what he was talking about
Just plain boring
Nice Biology professor. Knows what he is teaching.
he is pretty bad.. plus he is unorganized and doesnt have any lecture notes
Monotoned voice ... unable to stay awake in class
Aright Eckenwalder might sound a little dead, but overall he's a good prof. He covered all the topics in detail and that made studying for exams pretty easy. I would give him 8.5/10
if he wants to mumble, he shouldn't be teaching first year students.  he should go and do his research, where he can mumble to his phd students
monotoned, but knows his stuff.  Tricky tests
his periodic 'uhhs' and 'umms' put me to sleep! if im awake to listen to his lectures, i would comment on them...but i never seem to be able to stay awake...
All the caffeine in the world couldn't keep me awake in his classes tho. The course is super-theoretical to begin with, so his monotone voice doesn't help. But he knows his stuff.
He has a very soothing voice...but I fight to stay awake because the class has a million people in it. Not a bad prof, but not the best either. Knows what he's talking about though.

I hate being mean, but this prof speaks as if he's talking to people that have taken biology for years! And in his lecture guide he explains complex biological terms with other complex biological terms - that aren't explained themselves!

This is the most boring class I've ever taken--if I'm ever feeling sleep deprived, all I have to do is show up for his class.  It wouldn't be so bad, except that he speaks in the same monotonour tone--enough to put anyone to sleep!
